11. hoc uniuersum, ‘this Universe.' Unlike the Epicuream, who held that the Universe (τὸ πᾶν) contained innumerable worlds (κόσμοι), the Stoics believed in a single world placed at the centre of the Universe. Hence hoc is for them, but not for the Epicuream, an appropriate pronoun for the Universe.
